   - **Suggestion**: Use more descriptive variable names like `outerIndex` and `innerIndex`.
   - **Benefit**: Enhances code readability and makes it easier to understand the loop's purpose.

   ```java
   public void bubbleSort(int[] arr) {
       int n = arr.length;
       for (int outerIndex = 0; outerIndex < n - 1; outerIndex++) {
           for (int innerIndex = 0; innerIndex < n - outerIndex - 1; innerIndex++) {
               if (arr[innerIndex] > arr[innerIndex + 1]) {
                   int temp = arr[innerIndex];
                   arr[innerIndex] = arr[innerIndex + 1];
                   arr[innerIndex + 1] = temp;
               }
           }
       }
